rror=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kzr1665702743110.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kzr1665702743110.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kzr1665702743110.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kzr1665702743110\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When configuring the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD), you may encounter a variety of error situations, ranging from incorrectly displayed information to failure to connect to the server.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"kzr1665702743110__context_w7230ab1b5b1_w7231ab1b5_w7232ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kzr1665702743110__p_d23081e1_d23082e1_d23083e1\">When a problem persists after you have tried all possible solutions:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kzr1665702743110__li_d11339e1_d11340e1_d11341e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Close (all) running browsers and try again.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kzr1665702743110__li_d11342e1_d11343e1_d11344e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Close and restart all relevant Services (WWW publishing service, Java EE web server (such as Tomcat), Uniface Router) and try again.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529460\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529460\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface WRD Configuration Errors Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 When configuring the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD), you may encounter a variety of error situations, ranging from incorrectly displayed information to failure to connect to the server. When a problem persists after you have tried all possible solutions: Close (all) running browsers and try again. Close and restart all relevant Services (WWW publishing service, Java EE web server (such as Tomcat), Uniface Router) and try again. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}